					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja I. Year 16, day 36: 1000 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This records that <hi rend="italic">Rājarājavājya</hi>(for <hi rend="italic">vādya</hi>)<hi rend="italic">mārāyar</hi> enquired into the previous cash endowments to the temple and provided for an endowment of 10 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> for bathing the god with 108 <hi rend="italic">kalaśas</hi> on the day of Śadaiyam, the birth-day asterism of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
